	abstract = {The stormwater drainage network is an important component of urban infrastructure, and the interception well (IW), as a key facility of the stormwater drainage network, is mainly used to prevent combined sewer overflows (CSOs). The lack of models and knowledge regarding CSOs poses a significant challenge to the management of this issue, especially in the design and decision-making of IWs. To address this issue, this paper proposes a novel approach aimed at establishing a connection between CSOs and field data, especially enhancing the interpretability of IW field data. Initially, a digital twin framework for IWs is introduced, followed by the construction of a multi-source heterogeneous information fusion model for IWs based on digital twins and a digital twin-driven early warning method for CSOs, effectively correlating CSOs with field data. Finally, through a real-world case study, the effectiveness of the proposed method in early warning for CSOs is verified. © 2025 Elsevier Ltd},
